ter 1240","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","1191":"1191","Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hume","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish (Lowlands) and northern English: variant of   Hulme  , with loss of <i>l</i> before the bilabial consonant /m/, as in the vocabulary word <i>calm</i>. See   Holm   and   Home  .","Scottish: habitational name either from the barony of Home or from Hume (or Home) in Berwickshire, from which the barony took its name. The placename derives from Old English <i>hōum</i>, dative plural form of <i>hōh</i> ‘heel, spur of land’.","History: A family of this name (see 2 above) have held the Earldom of Home since 1605."],"variants":[{"name":"Humes","meanings":["English (Durham): variant of   Hume  , with excrescent <i>-s</i>, or a variant of   Holmes  ."]},{"name":"Hulme","meanings":["English: variant of   Holm   and of   Home   3 and 4."]},{"name":"Home","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Hume  .","English: variant of   Holm  .","English: habitational name from Home in Clifton on Teme or in Feckenham (Worcestershire) or from a minor place similarly named, a variant of   Hamm   (from Middle English <i>ham(me)</i>, with rounding of the vowel before the nasal consonant to give <i>hom(me)</i>)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Hume II was born in 1225, in Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, William Hume I, was 35 and his mother, Ada de Dunbar, was 34. He married Ada de Dunbar. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1299, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1225–1299":"1225–1299","1227–Female":"1227–Surnud","1260–1300":"1260–1300","1190–1266":"1190–1266","1191–1240":"1191–1240","1190":"1190","1227":"1227","1225":"1225","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","1299":"1299","after 1240":"pärast 1240","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","1191":"1191","Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1225–1299":"1225–1299","1227–Female":"1227–Kuollut","1260–1300":"1260–1300","1190–1266":"1190–1266","1191–1240":"1191–1240","1190":"1190","1227":"1227","1225":"1225","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","1299":"1299","after 1240":"1240 jälkeen","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","1191":"1191","Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1225–1299":"1225–1299","1227–Female":"1227–Décédée","1260–1300":"1260–1300","1190–1266":"1190–1266","1191–1240":"1191–1240","1190":"1190","1227":"1227","1225":"1225","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","1299":"1299","after 1240":"après 1240","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","1191":"1191","Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Hume II est né en 1225, à Hume, Berwickshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni, son père, William Hume I, avait 35 ans et sa mère, Ada de Dunbar, avait 34 ans. Il a épousé Ada de Dunbar. Ils ont eu au